title: ISic000105. I.Sicily inscription 000105
body:
Facsimile Images

1[---]RD[---]
2[---]..INPUB[---]
3[---].T.X.[---]

Apparatus criticus

Text from autopsy; The second letter shows no trace of a middle horizontal for 'E', while the lower stroke is both lighter and more curved than might be expected for E, suggesting possibly D (or L)?
3: The final letter could be P or R

translation

commentary

Bivona could not find the text, but it has been rediscovered in the museum stores.

bibliography

  • 23 https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137
  • Fiorelli NSA 1884 54 = 202 https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392
